  "texts": [
    "Although these studies have yielded promising results, it is clear that there is a significant lack of research on other ERP components, such as the P100 or N170.",
    "The absence of this research raises questions as to whether the strong outcomes found in P300 studies can be extrapolated to other components.",
    "Furthermore, the N170 is believed to reflect distinct cognitive processes (i.e., attentional gain to certain objects), whereas the P300 is a rather unspecific component which indexes several neuronal processes.",
    "Hence, the N170 is ideally suited to validate our new approach.",
    "Most importantly, the approaches presented above are not designed to discover a new ERP component, but rather show a way to detect a known one, assuming prior knowledge of its location and timing."
  ],
